# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — Claude Code project instructions

This project uses **Research Driven Development (RDD)**. The central unit is the
**experiment**; the central artifact is the **experiment card**.

{{ONE_LINE_PROJECT_DESCRIPTION}}

## Where things live

- **`PLAN.md` governs** — objectives, phases, gates, experiment matrix.
- Project map: `{{PROJECT_MAP_PATH}}` (orientation; don't duplicate its tree here).
- Experiment state: `experiments/registry.json` (source of truth) + `experiments/registry.html` (dashboard).
- Per-experiment cards: `experiments/E<seq>_<slug>/card.html`.
- Lab notebook: `notebook/NOTEBOOK.html`. Decisions: `decisions/`.

## Hard rules

- **One change per experiment.** More than one change = more than one card.
- **Gate criteria are declared on the card BEFORE launch.** Changing them later needs a dated decision entry.
- **Two human gates ⛔:** (1) researcher approves the card before any config/launcher/run; (2) researcher confirms the verdict before a gate is declared passed. Claude proposes; it never declares a gate passed.
- **No expensive/long compute without approval** — smoke test must pass locally first; cluster/paid runs are handed over to the human (`reference/compute-budget-policy.md`).
- **Frozen artifacts never mutate:** {{FROZEN_LIST_OR_NONE}}. Verify with `scripts/check_frozen.py`. Replacements get new names + a decision.
- **Every run is logged**, including failures and negative results. No deleting inconvenient runs.
- **Data sensitivity:** {{DATA_SENSITIVITY_RULES}}. Never upload, print, or commit: {{NEVER_LIST}}.
- **Domain constraints:** {{DOMAIN_SPECIFIC_CONSTRAINTS}}.

## Working style

- **Classify first:** infrastructure (mini-SDD: contract + tests before code) / experiment (the card loop) / analysis-writing (cited report).
- **Human-facing docs are styled HTML, never plain Markdown.** Cards, registry, notebook, analysis reports, infra-specs, and any other spec/design/proposal use the `research.css`/`research.js` design system (templates in `.claude/skills/research-workflow/templates/`; generic `doc.html.template` for anything else). Copy `research.css`/`research.js` next to a new artifact so it renders. Only operational files (`CLAUDE.md`, skills, agents, project map, decisions) stay Markdown.
- Smoke test before any cluster submission; runs are resumable by design.
- Claims trace to artifacts — every number cites a card or dataset ID.

